# Agnostic Seed — Cursor Rules

## Absolute constraints

- NEVER write `storage/**/*.json` directly. Use `npm run mcp:bridge` tools instead.
- NEVER edit `src/components/agnostic/**` or `packages/**` for project-specific changes.
- NEVER edit `src/generated/agnostic-schemas.ts` — it is auto-generated by `agnostic:compile`.
- NEVER use `Math.random()` or `Date.now()` for IDs — use `crypto.randomUUID()`.
- NEVER use camelCase in schema field keys, block data keys, or relation configs — snake_case only.

## Storage mutations → MCP bridge only

```bash
npm run mcp:bridge
# Tools: create_schema, update_schema, create_route, update_route, write_script, list_*, get_*
```

## Layer boundaries

```
packages/                    READ-ONLY (engine)
src/components/agnostic/     READ-ONLY (engine)
src/lib/agnostic/            READ-ONLY (engine)
src/app/api/                 READ-ONLY (engine)
agnostic.config.ts           WRITABLE  (register custom blocks here)
src/components/specialized/  WRITABLE  (custom UI — always default export, use _TEMPLATE.tsx)
storage/                     MCP ONLY  (never direct file writes)
```

## The invariant

```
block.context === schema.data.name === storage_file_name_without_extension
```

If these diverge, the engine renders nothing. No error. No log.

## Correct feature build sequence

1. `create_schema` (MCP) → define entity
2. `create_route` (MCP) → create URL
3. `npm run agnostic:compile` → sync TypeScript types
4. Create `src/components/specialized/YourBlock.tsx` (default export)
5. Register in `agnostic.config.ts` → `blocks: { type: () => import('./src/...') }`
6. `update_route` (MCP) → set `block.type = "your_type"` on the route
